{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a large stock pot (2-3 L) with water over high heat and bring to the boil. Carefully add ribs to boiling water and cook, until half cooked (approx. 7 minutes). Carefully remove with tongs, then drain and set aside.","Place garlic and chilli into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add blanched pork ribs, potato starch, sugar, pepper, salt, black bean sauce, oyster sauce, soy sauce and vinegar and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer ribs and marinade into a glass or ceramic bowl, cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator for a minimum of 1 hour to marinate (see Tips).","Place water into mixing bowl and place Varoma dish into position. Line Varoma dish with baking paper, poking a few small holes in paper to allow steam to circulate. Place ribs and marinade into Varoma dish, secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>40-50 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>, until ribs are cooked through. Garnish with spring onions\/shallots to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["600 - 800 g pork ribs, cut into ribs","800 g water, plus extra for for boiling","3 garlic cloves","1 fresh long red chilli, deseeded and cut in long pieces","1 tbsp potato starch","½ tsp white sugar","¼ tsp ground white pepper","¼ tsp salt","2 tbsp Chinese black bean sauce (see Tips)","1 tbsp oyster sauce","1 tbsp soy sauce","1 tbsp rice wine vinegar","1 - 2 spring onions\/shallots, cut into slices, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r313501","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-l0q76SPq338\/XZQFwtiCfwI\/AAAAAAAAb2c\/PbdMkXK6Dn8j8dAnrfLuNg1joU--dW3bACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_AY39Y3y3T1flToc7.png","title":"Pork ribs with black bean sauce","publishedAt":"2018-07-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{},"usefulItems":"plastic wrap, stock pot (3-4 L), ceramic or glass bowl, baking paper, wooden skewer, tongs, refrigerator, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["The ribs can be made ahead of time and allowed to marinate in the refrigerator for up to 8 hours before steaming."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","2h","2 portions"]}